  "instructions": [
    "Heat 1 tablespoon of ghee or oil in a pan over medium heat.",
    "Add cumin seeds and let them sizzle for a few seconds.",
    "Add onion, ginger, and garlic, and cook until the onion is translucent.",
    "Add green chilies, coriander powder, turmeric powder, and red chili powder, and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add split yellow peas, salt, and water, and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for 15 minutes.",
    "Meanwhile, heat 1 tablespoon of ghee or oil on the robata grill coals.",
    "Add 1 cup of cooked basmati rice to the grill and cook for 2-3 minutes, until lightly toasted.",
    "Repeat with the remaining rice and set aside.",
    "Once the peas are cooked, fluff them with a fork and add the toasted rice, chopped cilantro, and lemon juice.",
    "Mix well and serve hot.",
    "Garnish with additional cilantro and serve with lemon wedges on the side.",
    "Taste and adjust the seasoning as needed."
  ],
